My fourth year at Quest for the Crest 55k. Man, this course just never gets old. I gravitate to this race every spring given its perfect timing to really kick off big mountain running festivities. It always seems to give me just the training stimulus I need. 

However, I've grown to realize that it's the people who bring me back every year. To the volunteers and race staff at @runbumraces 🙏 you for the flawless race year after year. To the runners that somehow know who I am and show incredible support out on the trails, wow, incredibly grateful for all of you! 

As I told my family after the race, this was a stepping stone to something much bigger. Next stop, Hardrock 100.

I'll keep things short and sweet. Hardrock 100 was everything I imagined. My heart was full, and I was incredibly happy to have finally had my opportunity to run the race. 

I ran the first 80 miles fast hanging out in 3rd place for most of the day. Going into the night, I left Telluride (mile 75) feeling strong and inspired to move into 2nd place. A few miles up the trail, my body had other plans. After spending hours vomiting loads of bile, I finally made it to Ophir (mile 86) and took my first ever nap during a 100m race. After a few hours of contemplating life, I finally left the aid with Sabrina, who I have to thank for helping me make it to the finish line. 

I learn something about myself every time I do one of these events and look forward to the next big adventure ❤️

An extension of the body, are the @blackdiamond Carbon FLZ poles. 
Personally, I go 125 - 130 cm. I prefer to maximize the steps per pole plant, which means going with a little more length.

The new @methodseventrail "Silverton" is the real deal. It was so awesome to see so many trail runners this past week running around in the new M7s, a true trail running oriented piece of equipment. The Silverton was designed to be ultra-light and outperform all lens technology below treeline!

There were some pretty magical moments out there to be grateful for 🙏

📸 @vspicturescom

This weekend, I had the honor to pace my buddy @cindersmokeatx at the @crazymountainultra 100m. Bobby ran nothing short of the best race of his life. I can't thank him enough for allowing me to be a part of the process in his training and planning around the event. He respected the course and the race plan and executed like a true veteran. I'm incredibly inspired by his determination to grow as an athlete and am proud to coach such an inspiration. 🙏

Eyeing down some FKTs from the Bridger's to the Beartooths. Should be a fun week ahead!

Scenes from a new round trip speed record on Black Mountain (10,949 ft) in the Beartooth Wilderness. Dropped 1 hour and 37 minutes off the previous record. This route is totally rad, lots of tech, great alpine running, and lots of vert! The round trip comes out to somewhere around 12.5 - 13 miles with 6,000 ft of vertical gain. Unofficial (for now) new record time 03:03:32. 

And yes.... I listened to nothing but 80s and 90s classic country hits the whole run. Yesterday, a grizzly was wandering around the campsite/trailhead, so I felt it was a good idea to blast some tunes to let the locals know I was coming.
A vertical ⛰️ dream.

Shaved a few minutes off the Frosty Mt round trip record up in Manning Park, BC today. Speed seems to be coming back. I've made the tough decision to bail from TOR this year. Instead, I'll be racing UTMB - SLOVENIA 100K on Sept 8th.

My dude @uphillswagger getting the dub at Fat Dog 120 this past weekend. It was a real pleasure running the final 47 miles into the finish with this guy, especially as he dropped sub  8s on the final 4 mile stretch into the finish!

Gosh, I can't tell you how many brands of sunglasses I've tried over the years, but I know for sure it's a lot! 
The @methodseventrail Silvertons, without a doubt, take the cake on the best eyewear I've ever used. The Silvertons are a one-stop shop for trail running, road running, cycling, mtb, climbing, and paddleboarding for me when I'm headed out on my daily adventure.

One final FKT before I head to Europe on Sunday. Took 2 minutes off the Shriner Pk FKT in Ranier National Park today. The previous record was held by the PNW legend Uli Steidl. 
My uphill speed was pretty garbage today, so when I got to the summit, I knew I was going to have to blast some pretty fast splits down. Four sub 6:00 miles later, and I managed a new speed record.

SPEEDLAND ATHLETE GIVEBACK

Part of our brand mission is to support outdoor programs selected by our athlete partners. Over the next few weeks we’ll share what those organizations are and why — next up is @runninhigh. 

“I chose Trees Indiana because its where I first began my trail running journey. Fort Wayne, Indiana doesn’t have an abundance of trail running but the little trail running that is available in and around the city I want to help preserve. Those trails are my foundation as a runner and where it all began for me. I hope those trails can provide the same opportunity for others that they provided for myself.” 

Follow along for more on the 2023 athlete giveback over the next few weeks. And stay tuned for Avery’s footwear commission dropping in 2024. 👀🍿
